1
00:00:55,375 --> 00:01:01,833
[BEEZLEBUB cackling]

2
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:06,000
Bahamut has awakened,
and I herby pass my judgment!

3
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,833
Hear me, o gods.

4
00:01:07,916 --> 00:01:11,375
Our long-standing war
is over, and it is time

5
00:01:11,458 --> 00:01:15,833
to accept your defeat!
I find you unfit to rule!

6
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:17,708
Bow before me!

7
00:01:17,791 --> 00:01:21,291
And demons! Hear me, as well!

8
00:01:21,375 --> 00:01:27,958
You will etch my name into
eternity! I am Lord Beezlebub!

9
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:30,500
Our kind will stand above gods,

10
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:34,083
but I will be the
master above you all!

11
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:43,958
Now witness my power!
I control Bahamut itself!

12
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:52,041
[gasps]

13
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,375
[AZAZEL groaning]

14
00:01:59,458 --> 00:02:02,000
No, it isn't possible.

15
00:02:15,458 --> 00:02:17,583
[LAVALLEY]
Pure poetry.

16
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:27,875
Lavalley! What is this?
What's wrong with you?

17
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:30,166
Don't you see?
He was behind everything.

18
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:32,916
Gaining your trust, then
misdirecting you to Helheim.

19
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,708
Framing Jeanne D'Arc, and
turning her into a demon.

20
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:38,208
It was all part
of his deception.

21
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,625
And this was the goal.

22
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:41,500
He manipulated
everyone at once--

23
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:43,500
gods, demons, and humans alike.

24
00:02:43,583 --> 00:02:45,375
All so he could
bring back Bahamut.

25
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:49,000
[LAVALLEY cackles] Who knew a
zombie could be so smart?

26
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:12,625
t's all over, arf!

27
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:14,291
We're gonna be toast, arf!

28
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:15,000
[DOGS yelp]

29
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:17,125
But I don't wanna die!

30
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:20,166
[DOGS, CERBERUS scream]

31
00:03:31,541 --> 00:03:34,666
Lavalley! Who are you, really?

32
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:37,291
His true name is
Gilles de Rais.

33
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:40,333
He's a sorcerer with a bounty
and some kind of death wish--

34
00:03:40,416 --> 00:03:42,875
and he's taken countless
lives with his magic.

35
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:43,750
He's a bounty?

36
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:45,000
Yes.

37
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:46,875
I mean that's according
to the god of hangovers,

38
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:47,958
but it does seem to add up.

39
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:49,666
You used us!

40
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:54,666
Could you two please
keep it down?

41
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,541
I really can't have
you ruining the mood.

42
00:03:56,625 --> 00:03:58,208
[growls]

43
00:03:58,291 --> 00:04:00,958
This has taken me a great
deal of time and effort.

44
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:03,791
And now I want to savor
the end of the world.

45
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:05,125
You scoundrel!

46
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:09,000
[yells]

47
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,083
[LAVALLEY]
Did you not hear me?

48
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:13,541
Get away from him!

49
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:17,458
[KAISAR groans]

50
00:04:17,541 --> 00:04:20,916
When someone asks nicely,
it's polite to oblige.

51
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,458
But you seem determined to test
the sharpness of my blade.

52
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:26,458
His face is changing!

53
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:34,125
Don't you understand how
lucky you are to be here?

54
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:36,125
You fool. This is
the biggest moment

55
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,958
this reality has ever known.

56
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:41,083
[KAISAR grunts]

57
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:43,833
[LAVALLEY, MARTINET]
This is the world's destruction!

58
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,333
Can't you finally acknowledge

59
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:48,000
that life is pointless and
enjoy the beauty as it burns?

60
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:49,375
Let me go!

61
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:50,625
Damn.

62
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:58,625
Seems my body has
become a bit unstable.

63
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:00,208
Sorry for that.

64
00:05:00,291 --> 00:05:01,666
I think you've taken
one too many

65
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:03,791
of your dubious concoctions.

66
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:06,791
We're both stuck in
strange bodies now.

67
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:12,125
[grunts]

68
00:05:16,208 --> 00:05:18,541
[LAVALLEY] So the silly man
insists on playing knight

69
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:21,875
for a little longer. Fine.
If you refuse to sit still,

70
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:25,208
then maybe I'll have your
old friend keep you busy.

71
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:32,625
[gasps]

72
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:39,750
Well, now what? I already
used up all my antidotes.

73
00:06:08,708 --> 00:06:11,625
[BEEZLEBUB] I bore Amira
from my own demonic essence

74
00:06:11,708 --> 00:06:13,250
and magic power.

75
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:17,000
And used her as the vessel
that would unseal Bahamut.

76
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:21,333
You promised me if I did, that I
could bend the beast to my will.

77
00:06:21,416 --> 00:06:24,000
Curse you, Martinet, you lying--

78
00:06:28,541 --> 00:06:31,250
[AZAZEL]
There, you fool. We're even.

79
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:35,833
Although, it hardly matters now.

80
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:03,750
[CHARIOCE] No! I don't want
to die! I want to be the king!

81
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:08,375
Please, Mother!
You have to protect me!

82
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:10,958
Mother! Mommy!

83
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:14,750
[CHARIOCE screams]

84
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:21,875
[KAISAR grunting]

85
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:28,333
[gasps]

86
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:31,666
[inaudible]

87
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:34,125
[gasps]

88
00:07:34,208 --> 00:07:37,083
Rita! I'm going to settle
things once and for all!

89
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:39,250
Stay out of this fight!

90
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:47,458
You idiot! This is hardly the
time for your stupid feud!

91
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:50,125
[KAISAR grunting]

92
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:11,666
[RITA gasping]

93
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,791
[KAISAR grunting]

94
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:15,625
[RITA screams]

95
00:08:20,916 --> 00:08:22,958
[KAISAR grunts]

96
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:44,333
[KAISAR screams]

97
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:46,083
Kaisar!

98
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,500
Now, that's the sort
of entertainment

99
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:14,375
I've been looking for.

100
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:16,833
[FAVARO]
Got some advice for ya.

101
00:09:16,916 --> 00:09:18,166
[LAVALLEY grunts]

102
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,291
[FAVARO] When you're walkin'
around with a bounty

103
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:20,625
on your head,
there're a few things

104
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:25,833
you should probably watch
out for. For example...

105
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:28,958
Seel Soh... Cetom!

106
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:32,833
[gasps]

107
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:40,458
[gasps, screams]

108
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:50,208
...getting too close to a knight
who's still walkin' around

109
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:53,333
with a bracelet from his
old bounty hunter days.

110
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:01,583
[KAISAR groaning]

111
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:02,958
[RITA]
Okay, talk.

112
00:10:03,041 --> 00:10:05,083
When exactly did you
turn back to normal?

113
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,583
What, you can't guess?

114
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,208
It was when Kaisar gave me
that bi-otch of a wake-up call.

115
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:12,458
But how did that work?

116
00:10:12,541 --> 00:10:14,250
I managed to catch
one of your antidotes

117
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:15,875
that you dropped.

118
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:18,666
Then I stuck it in the head
of the crossbow bolt.

119
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:21,458
And then Kaisar and I
just put on a little show

120
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:23,958
to convince that freak I was
still his faithful servant.

121
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:26,000
Though, I swear when we
started, I didn't think

122
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,416
I'd be lopping off your hand.

123
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:29,416
I have no regrets.
It was the only way

124
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,791
to convince that trickster.

125
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,708
So amputation was seriously
the best idea you had?

126
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:34,375
Idiots.

127
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:35,500
[KAISAR groans]

128
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:37,083
[BACCHUS]
Nice work.

129
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,166
[FAVARO]
Damn!

130
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:41,000
Looks like you got thrashed.

131
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:43,416
[BACCHUS] Yeah, I have the
lunatic to think for that.

132
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,750
His reward better be
down right handsome.

133
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,291
That's an understatement.

134
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:50,333
This bad boy's worth more than
even you can spend in a day.

135
00:10:50,416 --> 00:10:53,791
If that's a dare, then I
gladly accept. Although...

136
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:57,833
[FAVARO] I doubt I'll be hitting
the taverns anytime soon.

137
00:10:57,916 --> 00:11:00,458
[KAISAR] You think you
can reach Lady Amira?

138
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:04,291
[FAVARO] Don't know.
But it's up to me to find out.

139
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:07,291
Does that mean you've decided
what you're going to do?

140
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,291
I'll go with you, Favaro.

141
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:13,125
Are you delusional,
or did you forget

142
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,666
you're down to one hand?

143
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,291
Hey, Kaisar.

144
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:20,458
I have to kill Amira.

145
00:11:20,541 --> 00:11:21,666
Cut it out.

146
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:24,458
Now's not the time for
your foolish jokes.

147
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:28,333
You see me laughing?

148
00:11:28,416 --> 00:11:30,083
How could you even
say those words?

149
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:32,083
She fused with Bahamut--
it was permanent.

150
00:11:32,166 --> 00:11:34,625
She'll be a part of him
as long as she's alive.

151
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:37,625
So I'm going to have to kill
her. It's the only option left.

152
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:39,666
There must be some
other way to save her!

153
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,916
We have to keep trying!

154
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:45,250
[FAVARO]
There's not. It's too late.

155
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,583
The dragon in the
forest told me.

156
00:11:56,458 --> 00:11:58,291
[KAISAR]
But I swore.

157
00:11:58,375 --> 00:12:01,833
I swore that I'd save her,
no matter what it took.

158
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:06,541
I can't let you kill her.
I have to bring her back alive!

159
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:13,416
[FAVARO]
We can't get her out, Kaisar.

160
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,291
But I can save her, in a way.

161
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:19,958
Save her from suffering inside
that beast for eternity.

162
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:23,458
That's why I need
to do this. For her.

163
00:12:23,541 --> 00:12:26,625
Bacchus. Any idea how
I can get up there?

164
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:28,875
We can think of one way.
Right, Hamsa?

165
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:29,750
What?

166
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:30,958
You'll carry him there yourself!

167
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:32,416
[HAMSA squaks]

168
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,875
[KAISAR]
Wait. I'm coming, too.

169
00:12:41,958 --> 00:12:43,500
Did I change your mind?

170
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:46,458
Never! I'm going to bring
her back from Bahamut,

171
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:48,500
no matter what you say!

172
00:12:54,458 --> 00:12:57,000
Be back soon! Either that
or we'll be dead!

173
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:58,958
[groans]

174
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:05,208
--[HAMSA grunts]
--[FAVARO, KAISAR yelp]

175
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,875
[FAVARO, KAISAR scream]

176
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:34,000
[HAMSA yelps]

177
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:36,666
This is nuts!
I can't get closer!

178
00:13:39,541 --> 00:13:41,666
Then You have to
keep trying! Please!

179
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:43,291
[HAMSA grunts]

180
00:13:48,083 --> 00:13:50,666
[HAMSA yelps]
Hot! Hot! Hot!

181
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:53,875
Can't it stop breathing
fire for a freakin' minute?

182
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,541
Look at that!

183
00:14:45,041 --> 00:14:46,541
That's our cue!

184
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,625
[FAVARO, KAISAR grunt]

185
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:20,958
[FAVARO, KAISAR groan]

186
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:23,958
[KAISAR grunts]

187
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:25,333
[FAVARO]
Gotcha!

188
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:34,791
[KAISAR, FAVARO yelling]

189
00:15:36,541 --> 00:15:39,291
[FAVARO, KAISAR panting]

190
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:47,333
[FAVARO, KAISAR yelp]

191
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:51,750
[KAISAR, FAVARO grunt]

192
00:15:54,541 --> 00:15:55,416
[BOTH grunt]

193
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,166
[FAVARO yelps]

194
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,375
[KAISAR grunts]

195
00:16:16,625 --> 00:16:19,875
[FAVARO grunts]

196
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,208
[gasps] Hey! Favaro!

197
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:39,083
[FAVARO grunting]

198
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,208
So it's you?

199
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,041
[FAVARO grunting]

200
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:48,500
[BAHAMUT roaring]

201
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:50,541
[yells]

202
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:53,416
Amira!

203
00:17:19,416 --> 00:17:21,291
[gasps]

204
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,041
The Holy Knight. It's you.

205
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:32,000
[KAISAR grunting]

206
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:34,000
[FAVARO yelping]

207
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:35,916
[KAISAR]
Favaro!

208
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:40,166
[FAVARO yelping]

209
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:43,208
[FAVARO]
Oh... ah, ha...

210
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:44,250
Come on.

211
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:46,416
Don't'cha know it's
rude to stare?

212
00:17:57,791 --> 00:17:58,833
[FAVARO]
Amira.

213
00:17:58,916 --> 00:17:59,958
[AMIRA]
You finally came.

214
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:01,458
Well, yeah!

215
00:18:01,541 --> 00:18:03,791
Ha! I couldn't let you run
off when you still haven't

216
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:06,208
taken this tail
off me, now could I?

217
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:12,250
Ah! Don't cry, that a was
a bad joke! Look, Amira.

218
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:14,000
I came despite the
odds 'cause I care

219
00:18:14,083 --> 00:18:16,416
and can't stand to
see you in trouble.

220
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:20,291
It's always been that way.
Ever since we met.

221
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:21,208
You're lying.

222
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:23,125
I'm not lying!

223
00:18:23,208 --> 00:18:26,250
And I'm sorry things didn't go
better with you and your mom.

224
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,875
You deserved more.

225
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:32,791
Don't be sorry. She really
did recognize me.

226
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:35,500
At the very end,
when I was hugging her.

227
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:38,208
Seriously?

228
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:39,833
It was just like you said!

229
00:18:39,916 --> 00:18:41,208
Well, I am smart guy.

230
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:42,708
[AMIRA giggles]

231
00:18:42,791 --> 00:18:44,125
But listen, Amira.

232
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:45,916
You got a good trip
ahead of you.

233
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,708
This time I'm taking you
to a way better place

234
00:18:47,791 --> 00:18:49,833
than stupid Helheim.

235
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:54,166
It's gonna be full
of beautiful things.

236
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:55,750
I can't wait for you to see.

237
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,166
Liar.

238
00:18:57,250 --> 00:19:00,875
I am not lying! Look!
Are these the eyes of a liar?

239
00:19:00,958 --> 00:19:03,041
Hmmm!

240
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:33,625
Thank you, Favaro.

241
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:57,833
Hold on a second.
I don't think this is over.

242
00:20:03,041 --> 00:20:05,333
[HAMSA]
Hurry! Jump on so we can go!

243
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:08,083
I can't! He's still
down there!

244
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:15,875
[growls]

245
00:20:15,958 --> 00:20:17,250
[KAISAR grunts]

246
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:30,041
[FAVARO grunting]

247
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,458
[FAVARO screams]

248
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:49,625
Favaro!

249
00:21:07,583 --> 00:21:09,041
[LEAD KNIGHT 12A]
Sir Kaisar.

250
00:21:09,125 --> 00:21:11,041
If you're going to address
the troops as my lieutenant,

251
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:12,791
you'd better come now.

252
00:21:16,583 --> 00:21:19,333
[LEAD KNIGHT 12A] Today is the
coronation of our new king.

253
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:22,416
And we, the royal Orlêans
Knights, are tasked with...

254
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,458
Is Lieutenant Kaisar here yet?

255
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:30,000
[BARTENDER 12A]
They say that just when Bahamut

256
00:21:30,083 --> 00:21:31,833
was about to destroy the world,

257
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:33,625
The Holy Knight
of legend showed up

258
00:21:33,708 --> 00:21:36,833
and banished it to some other
realm or dimension or something.

259
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:39,208
You think that means
the monster's dead?

260
00:21:41,375 --> 00:21:42,666
Not a chance.

261
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:46,208
Bahamut can't be killed.
Not now. Not ever.

262
00:21:48,541 --> 00:21:49,958
